# Immutable Audit Log

## Requirement

Every user action that creates/updates/deletes domain data must write an `AuditLog` row. **Append-only** — no UPDATE or DELETE on audit rows, including for IT admin.

## Required fields per entry

| Field | Content |
|-------|---------|
| `user_id` / `user_name` | Actor identity |
| `action` | e.g. create, update, view, dispense, print_quote |
| `description` | Human-readable summary |
| `tag` | Module: patients, medical, technical, financial, warehouse |
| `logged_at` | Server-synced timestamp (second precision) |
| `ip_address` / `mac_address` | Device fingerprint when available |
| `payload_before` / `payload_after` | JSON snapshot of changed fields |

## Implementation rules

- Write audit in **Service layer** after successful transaction commit
- Never log secrets (passwords, tokens)
- Failed validations do not audit unless security-relevant (e.g. blocked dispense)
- Admin UI: read-only listing + export; no edit/delete routes for `AuditLog`

## Legal weight

Treat audit table as legal evidence — migrations must not add ON DELETE CASCADE from audit to mutable entities.
